g.aria-label: When the edges of a complete graph with 10 nodes are colored red or blue, there is a subgraph with 4 nodes where all edges are red or a subgraph with 3 nodes where all edges are blue.
Either the top node is connected to at least 6 nodes by a red edge.
Or it is connected to at least 4 nodes by a blue edge.
The search for a subgraph can be restricted to these 6 nodes.
The new top node is again connected to at least 3 nodes by only red or blue edges.
We can use the previous top node to extend a red triangle.
Either all edges between these 4 nodes are red, or one edge is blue
